# Semantic HTML Usage in SolidJS + Vite

## 🚨 **CRITICAL: Use Div Elements Only**

**MANDATORY**: This SolidJS + Vite application uses **div elements exclusively** for all content (except `<i>` for icons) to avoid conflicts with Tailwind CSS default browser styles.

**Rule**: Use `div` elements with Tailwind classes instead of semantic HTML elements.

## ❌ **FORBIDDEN: Semantic HTML Elements**

### ❌ **Never Use Semantic HTML Elements**

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG: Semantic HTML elements
<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold">Title</h1>
<h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold">Subtitle</h2>
<h3 class="text-2xl font-medium">Heading</h3>
<p class="text-base">Paragraph text</p>
<section class="mb-8 p-4">Content section</section>
<header class="bg-background">Header content</header>
<footer class="bg-muted">Footer content</footer>
<nav class="flex space-x-4">Navigation</nav>
<main class="flex-1">Main content</main>
<aside class="w-64">Sidebar</aside>
<article class="prose">Article content</article>
<span class="text-sm">Inline text</span>
```

### ❌ **Never Use Form Elements**

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG: Form elements
<form class="space-y-4">
  <label class="block">Label</label>
  <input type="text" class="w-full" />
  <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>

// ❌ WRONG: List elements
<ul class="space-y-2">
  <li>List item 1</li>
  <li>List item 2</li>
</ul>

<ol class="space-y-2">
  <li>Ordered item 1</li>
  <li>Ordered item 2</li>
</ol>
```

